7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"Protect and improve biodiversity performance by implementing ISO 14001"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:30:54+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"the important factors that most of the businesses believe are protection and improvement of biodiversity. Hence, by implementing ISO 14001 your business can"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Protect and improve biodiversity performance by implementing ISO 14001"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"The meaning of Biodiversity is that, the endurance of organizations relies on environment services, various species, and qualities. Nowadays, the important factors that most of the businesses believe are protection and improvement of biodiversity. Hence, by implementing ISO 14001 your business can protect and improve biodiversity."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Biodiversity"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"The various references of biodiversity can be found in ISO 14001:2015. The corrected version of the ISO 14001 standard need to address future difficulties, where the loss of diversity is one of the essential ones.The mandatory requirements are not related to biodiversity in ISO 14001:2015, its importance has been upgraded in the new standards and it is reflected in the content."}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"There is a new approach in ISO 14001:2015 which gives more attention to biodiversity for the identification of the environmental effects. While in the previous version, the company had to decide its impacts on the environment, but in the revised version of ISO 14001 certification standard, there is a difference in context, and the company must find out the impacts from the environment that influence its activities and processes."}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Business consequences • Direct Effects"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Organizations' activities can have significant negative consequences, both direct and indirect effects."}],["$","p","7",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Direct impacts are the introduction of non-local species that can upset the environments, habitat corruption by the utilization of land, and overflow of rainfall to distributed land that leads to the contamination of streams. When an organization executes ISO 14001:2015, these direct effects are resolved, just as the ability to do the essential activities to relieve those direct negative effects."}],["$","p","8",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"• Indirect Effects"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Indirect Effects arecaused by third parties or outsiders during the production processes. Another indirect effect is caused by a consumer who uses or disposesof the goods. ISO 14001:2015 expects suppliers to be chosen by specific rules depending on the protection of the environment and its biodiversity. Hence this rule reduces the indirect effects by conducting required activities to diminish or maintain a strategic distance from the related effects. For instance, although an organization can't control whether a client is discarding an item effectively, it can compose the proper guidelines demonstrating the most ideal approach to dispose or reuse that thing."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b"]}],"$L1c"]}]}]
